Components of UNIX:
----------------------
2 important Components :
      Shell
      Kernel

Shell :
-----------
It is the outer layer of UNIX operating system.
Shell reads command provided by the user.
Shell will check whether it is valid command or not.
Shell will check if it is properly used or not.
If everything is proper, then shell interprets/converts that command into kernel understandable form and handover that to the kernel 

Kernel :
------------
It is the core component of UNIX operating system.
It is responsible to execute our commands with the help of hardware components.
Memory allocation and processor allocation will be taken care of by kernel.
It acts as interface between shell and hardware components.

User/Application ----> Shell ----> Kernel ----> hardware


